Installing and loading the packages

First, lets install the packages for producing the graphs. These packages are avaliable in the CRAN repository:

#set mirror
local({r <- getOption("repos")
       r["CRAN"] <- "http://cran.r-project.org"
       options(repos=r)})
if(!require(CMplot, quietly = T)){
  install.packages("CMplot")
} # For the manhattan plots
## Much appreciate for using CMplot.
## Full description, Bug report, Suggestion and the latest codes:
## https://github.com/YinLiLin/CMplot
if(!require(gplots, quietly = T)){
  install.packages("gplots")
} # For beautiful heatmaps
## 
## Attaching package: 'gplots'
## The following object is masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     lowess
library(CMplot)
library(gplots)

Installing GAPIT functions

For performing the GWAS, we will be using the package GAPIT. The package GAPIT is a suite of programs developed in R, and it contains several models to perform GWAS. Since the developers actively maintain the package. We will be installing the package directly from Dr.Zhang Labs website:

Downloading the example dataset

For the Lab class today, we will be performing GWAS in a maize example dataset. The source of the dataset is Tassels GitHub page: https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://github.com/maize-genetics/rTASSEL__;!!DZ3fjg!6WdLofoS7t5xdmklXdtwOEWiSMbth9NXs-0l6vFG92_gr9gesDRICsYM22BXF8CAziHf8kCDWrT91wHxilemhYP4hbU4$

phenot <- read.table(url("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/maize-genetics/rTASSEL/master/inst/extdata/mdp_traits.txt"), header = T)
genot <- read.delim(url("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/maize-genetics/rTASSEL/master/inst/extdata/mdp_genotype.hmp.txt"), header = F)

Performing the GWAS

gapit_result <- GAPIT(Y = subset(phenot, select = c("X.Trait.", "EarHT")),
                      G = genot,
                      model = "MLM",
                      PCA.total = 3)

SNP Density Plot

CMplot(Pmap = subset(x = gapit_result$GWAS, select = c("SNP", "Chromosome", "Position ", "P.value")),
       LOG10 = T,
       threshold = 0.01,
       col = rainbow(n = 10), file.output = FALSE, plot.type = "d")

Circular Manhattan Plot

CMplot(Pmap = subset(x = gapit_result$GWAS, select = c("SNP", "Chromosome", "Position ", "P.value")),
       LOG10 = T,
       threshold = 0.01,
       col = rainbow(n = 10),
       file.output = FALSE,
       plot.type = "c",
       outward = F,
       H = 5,
       r = 10,
       cir.band = 5,
       amplify = F,
       band = 1)
